Read RNAseq counts

read_counts.Rd

Read tsv file with rnaseq counts into SummarizedExperiment

read_counts(
  file,
  fid_col = 1,
  fname_col = character(0),
  filter_features_min_count = 10,
  verbose = TRUE,
  plot = TRUE
)

Arguments

file

string: path to rnaseq counts file
fid_col

number of name of column with feature identifiers
fname_col

string or number: feature name variable
filter_features_min_count

number (default 10): filter out features with less than 10 counts (in the smallest library) across samples. Filtering performed with filterByExpr
verbose

TRUE (default) or FALSE
plot

TRUE (default) / FALSE

Value

SummarizedExperiment

Details

File format: header row feature annotations in first few columns feature counts in next columns

See also

merge_sdata, merge_fdata

Examples

file <- download_data('billing19.rnacounts.txt')
read_counts(file)

#> 	Read: ~/importomicscache/datasets/billing19/billing19.rnacounts.txt
#> 		Guess subgroup values: EM00_R1 => EM00
#> 		Guess replicate values from sampleids: EM00_R1 => R1
#> 		Write design (update if required!): ~/importomicscache/datasets/billing19/billing19.rnacounts.design.txt
#> 		Keep 21990/56268 features: count >= 10 in at least some samples
#> 		TMM normalize and log2transform
#> 		Return object: counts(object)  = counts
#> 		               exprs(object)   = log2cpm
#> 		               weights(object) = voom weights (see plot)
#> 		               object$subgroup = subgroup values
#> class: SummarizedExperiment 
#> dim: 21990 24 
#> metadata(3): analysis file platform
#> assays(3): counts exprs weights
#> rownames(21990): ENSG00000000003.14 ENSG00000000005.5 ...
#>   ENSG00000283667.1 ENSG00000283674.1
#> rowData names(5): feature_id gene_id gene_name gene_type locus
#> colnames(24): EM00_R1 EM00_R2 ... BM_R2 BM_R3
#> colData names(6): sample_id subgroup ... libsize.filtered
#>   libsize.scaled
